> while it might NOT be the cause exactly, i've seen something similar on
> a 1979 camper bus ... and it turned out to be the exhaust/muffler was
> rusted and clogged. it would idle just fine and as long as you didn't
> put any sort of load on the engine (trying to drive), it would rev up.
> but as soon as you put it into gear and drive off, it would act like it
> had no power at all. and would not rev up past 3000 rpm at all. turned
> out to be the muffler was rusted shut inside, from heat rust.


